          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1CANTMF"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The experiment was carried out at the",
                "ISAC-I radioactive beam facility at TRIUMF. The ion",
                "beam was accelerated first by RFQ and then",
                "postaccelerated using a drift tube linac."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Windowless gas target filled with H2 at a pressure of",
                "5 Torr. The beam energy was chosen in order to cover",
                "a center-of mass energy range Ecm = 447-465 keV",
                "across the volume of the gas target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Array of 30 bismuth germanate (BGO) detectors",
                "surrounding the windowless gas target was used to",
                "detect gamma rays resulting from the (p,gamma)",
                "reaction,"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 20Na6+ recoils were transmitted to the focal",
                "plane of DRAGON spectrometer and were identified using",
                "time-of-flight system and an isobutane-filled",
                "ionization chamber"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time-of-flight (TOF) system was based on two",
                "microchannel plates detecting secondary electron",
                "emission from thin diamondlike carbon foils."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ionization chamber was used to determine",
                "energy of recoil ions"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Number of incident 19Ne ions was determined by",
                "measuring 19Ne beta decays in two 6-mm-thick plastic",
                "scintillators located near an intermediate focus of",
                "the separator where the 6+ component of the unreacted",
                "beam was stopped."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE",
                "GSPEC",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Inverse kinematics was used"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " An intense radioactive beam (RIB) of 19Ne in",
                "a 1+ charge state was produced by bombarding a SiC",
                "target with 500 MeV protons. Products of mass approx.",
                "19 amu were extracted and ionized in a Forced",
                "Electron Beam Induced Arc Discharge ion source and",
                "filtered using a high resolution mass separator. This",
                "beam was then injected into a radio-frequency",
                "quadrupole accelerator for an initial acceleration.",
                "The average 19Ne beam intensity was found to be",
                "approx. 7E+6 ions per sec."
              ]
            }
          ],
